args: One day, Sarisse and Luca visited their parents\nfor the first time in a long while...
Oh, thank heavens you're all right!
'Course we are! Neither of us is\ngoing down without a fight!
Do you have ANY idea how worried your\nfather and I have been, young man?!
Ha ha! You two haven't changed a bit!
Still, I'm surprised you guys are all still\nhiding out in the forest here.
I know the Empire leveled our village,\nbut I thought you'd have rebuilt by now.
There's a reason for that, unfortunately.
You see, Imperial soldiers are still\npatrolling the area.
But I thought the prince drove all those\ncrumbums outta here!
He didâ€”for a while, at least.
But a little after Sarisse left, they started\ncausing trouble again.
Who the hell are these guys?!\nFall back! Fall baaack!
Well, I've been learning a lot fighting\nwith {player_name}.
You're the best, Luca. Thanks for saving us!
You really have grown since I last saw you.\nYou took care of those soldiers as if\nthey were children's playthings.
If you were to stay here and protect us,\nwe might even be able to rebuild.\nWould you perhaps consider this?
I wish I could. Really I do.
But I made a promise to fight with\n{player_name}.
Yes, I see. Pray forgive me for asking\nthis of you.
When you left our village, you said you\ndid so in order to help us all.
And would not staying in the village\nmore readily allow you to do so?
Well, I suppose that's true, but...
I...I need some time to think about this.\nCan you wait until tomorrow?
I thought I knew what I wanted, but now...
You okay, Sarisse? I can lend you a\nbig floppy ear if you want it.
See, the more I think about it, the more I\nthink the elder is right. If I want to help\npeople, I should stay here and do that.
...But there's more to it than that, right?
I mean, I KNOW that makes sense,\nand yet...
Deep down, I just want to keep fighting\nwith {player_name}.
I think I get what you're saying.
That's exactly how I felt when I decided\nto leave the village and join up with\n{player_name}'s merry band.
Yep. There's just something about him.
The moment I met him, I felt like I could\naccomplish the thing I desired most.
It's...I dunno. My dream, I guess.
Yeah, but what IS your dream?
No way I'm telling you that!\nIt's too embarrassing.
I don't care who you are!\nThese lips are zipped.
All that matters here is that I understand\nwhere you're coming from, right?
Yeah, but I don't really have a dream\nor...whatever.
But you might find one if you stick with\n{player_name} long enough.
So THAT'S why I want to be with him!
Heh. Sounds like you've got your answer.
I'm sorry, everyone. But I've thought about\nthis a lot, and I'm going to keep fighting\nwith {player_name}.
This is how I'm going to fight to bring\npeace to everyone.
And it's also how I'm going to discover\nwhat I want to do with my life.

Sarisse wants to find her dream, and you
can bet whatever she comes up with is
going to be way bigger and better than all
of us here!
Supporting the dreams of children is the\nduty of parentsâ€”and of ALL adults.
But what will happen to us?\nWhat are we to do the next time\nthe soldiers come back?
We'll have to learn to defend ourselves.\nWe cannot keep placing that onerous\ntask on the backs of our children.
It's been a long time since I've had a good\nscrap; I'm looking forward to it!
Go forth and live your life, Sarisse.\nWe will keep your people safe.
